ZH: 他总是很主见，不轻易相信别人的意见。
EN: He always sticks to his own views and doesn't easily trust others' opinions.

ZH: 她是一个很有主见的人，不会随波逐流。
EN: She is a very opinionated person and won't go with the flow.

ZH: 我们需要一个有主见的领导来带领我们。
EN: We need a decisive leader to guide us.

ZH: 小明在班上是个有主见的学生，总是能够找到解决问题的方法。
EN: Xiaoming is a decisive student in the class, always able to find solutions to problems.

ZH: 你应该更加主见，不要被别人左右。
EN: You should be more decisive and not be influenced by others.

ZH: 她的主见导致了团队内部的分裂。
EN: Her strong opinions caused division within the team.

ZH: 作为老师，他应该具备一定的主见。
EN: As a teacher, he should have a certain degree of decisiveness.

ZH: 这个项目需要有主见的人来领导。
EN: This project needs someone with strong opinions to lead.

ZH: 我们需要一个能够做出决策的人，而不是一个缺乏主见的人。
EN: We need someone who can make decisions, not someone who lacks decisiveness.

ZH: 他总是能够快速做出决策，因为他有很强的主见。
EN: He is always able to make quick decisions because he has strong opinions.

ZH: 妈妈是最有主见的人，她总是知道该怎么做。
EN: Mom is the most opinionated person, she always knows what to do.

ZH: 领导者应该有自己的主见，并且能够坚定地支持自己的决定。
EN: Leaders should have their own opinions and be able to confidently support their decisions.

ZH: 她是一个很有主见的设计师，总是能够很好地表达自己的创意。
EN: She is a very decisive designer, always able to express her creativity well.

ZH: 他开始变得越来越有主见，能够独立思考问题。
EN: He is becoming more and more opinionated, able to think independently.

ZH: 老板对员工缺乏主见感到很失望。
EN: The boss is disappointed by the lack of decisiveness among the employees.

ZH: 小王是个很有主见的人，对于未来总是有清晰的规划。
EN: Xiaowang is a very opinionated person, always having clear plans for the future.

ZH: 希望团队中的每个人都能够更加主见，勇敢地提出自己的想法。
EN: Hopefully, everyone in the team can be more decisive and bravely voice their opinions.

